title: For Sale:  Federal auto match 22LR, Federal 9mm, Winchester 5.56
postcontent:
Anyone who pays upwards of $30 or more for Federal Auto match should be slapped.
Don't let the name fool you. It is certainly one of the better target and plinking ammunitions, and the powder burns relatively clean so it will function well in semi-autos, but it is definitely not "match grade competition" ammo.
Stop feeding the scalpers and prolonging this high priced and unavailable ammo nonsense!
In less than the last 60 days I have been able to get Federal Auto Match for $14.27 a box, Federal 9mm 100 round pack for $22.97, and Winchester 5.56 20 round box for $12.27 at only 2 nearby walmarts just by wandering in when I have free time and asking for it. Even the local gun shops are only running about 5% higher than last year, with the exception of a few who are acting like scalpers and will never get my business again.
I can appreciate selling ammo you don't need and making a couple extra bucks in these interesting times, but buying everything off the shelves and reselling at as much as 5 times the cost is BS!
It only takes a little patience and the ability to say "NO, I will not take it in the rear for ammo", and you too can buy it in the store again for a fair price.
This is a manipulated market and the scalpers are scaring you into buying from them by getting it before you can at the store. If you don't buy from them, they don't have the money to buy it out from under you anymore. Let them choke on it! 
I bought the Auto Match 22 LR just last week!
I bought my 3 boxes and left the rest for other customers. I did not take my whole family and buy it all.
Just take your time and don't expect to find it immediately. It took 2 months of going to the stores and most of the time leaving with nothing to get these. I like to use walmart.com too. It will give you a heads up as to what they've got.
Winchester 22 LR 555 round boxes were all over recently for around $25.00 but sold out fast. They'll be back soon. a little here and there, but the more the scalpers cannot afford to buy, the more we will start to find on the shelves again. Slow at first, then a lot. Hang tough and don't get robbed. In the last 2 weeks both cabellas and midway usa both sold 1000 round boxes of M-22 Winchester 22lr for nearly $50 a box. They sold out fast, but they had it at a FAIR price.

title: For Sale:  Mauser K98 (russian capture) with Scope Rings
postcontent:
I have had an advertisement up for my Russian Capture K98. I have received multiple emails, but none of the responders read the advertisement or met the criteria. Very simple, I am posting again and will put all the information I have. I am selling it at lower price, as I have other projects (non firearm related) I am working on, and would like to get going on those projects.

Firstly, I will only deal local face to face, no shipping on this rifle. 

I have had people ask about manufacture, age, caliber- Here is the down and dirty.

K98 (Mauser) used by the Nazi German military during world war 2. 

This is a Czech manufactured Mauser. As the Germans moved east they captured firearms manufacturing companies that had tooling and were producing mauser rifles and integrated them into their production. This rifle was manufactured in 1944, it was later captured by the Russians and while the Swastika and proof eagle and still visible, and stamped, the Swastika has been stamped out (now just an indent) the Eagle remains. The rifle is not original matching, as no Russian capture rifle was (to my knowledge) they were sent to various countries in the eastern bloc where they were disassembled, cleaned, and rebuilt and then electro penciled (so since the re-arsenal the rifle is matching). 

The rifle was brought in by Century, (probably the 90s?) and has the import mark hidden under the barrel (something they are not allowed to do anymore, and why all their imports have the ugly mark on the receiver) It was drilled and tapped and has reproduction high turret scope rings (repros go 100-200 dollars online) It has a scope (american made, non repro to original, Redfield 6x zoom). Currently the scope is not mounted or bore sighted, as I have been shooting irons. 

Rifle Details-
8mm caliber
Bore in excellent shape
Action clean and smooth
Usual milsurp wear and tear, no major flaws or damage
Shoots straight and with military ball ammo and iron sights I was getting sub 5 inch groups at 150 yards, I am sure with better ammo and the scope it shoots better. 

I will also include the scope, turret mounts (can see iron sights with scope attached) as well as 15 rounds of 8mm mauser (milsurp). 

M44 Nagant pictured with mauser has already been sold.
